      <item>
        <title>Contact forms 2022</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[ni.bonev]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>What you did will work.<br>
I can also give you another suggestion. Please take this with a grain of salt as it depends on a few factors weather its the right solution for you.</p>
<p>So in our case, sometimes we have forms where we want to create a special experience but we still want to use our WP server to automate the transactional stuff like emails.</p>
<p>What we do in that case is use CF7 in Wordpress to create a form with all its mailers and fields. You will then be able to submit content to that form via the REST api.</p>
<p>Endpoint looks like this: <code>/contact-form-7/v1/contact-forms/(?P&lt;id&gt;\\d+)/feedback</code><br>
You can of course find the info for all your endpoints by going to <a href="http://yourdomain.com/wp-json/" class="inline-onebox" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">yourdomain.com</a></p>
<p>Good luck. I hope that helps.</p>
          <p><a href="https://community.frontity.org/t/contact-forms-2022/6127/2">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
